headline: Procter & Gamble (NYSE:PG) Is a Dividend King Worth Watching
summary: In income investing, durability is of the utmost importance. This is because the idea of dividend investing is to one day rely on passive income to pay for living expenses. That can only be done if the underlying dividend payers in a portfolio have business models that are resilient enough to endure business cycle downturns. headline: Data Quality Driving Regulatory Reporting Decision-Making, according to S&P Global Market Intelligence Cappitech Survey
summary: S&P Global Market Intelligence today released the findings of its annual Global Regulatory Reporting Survey, highlighting that the most notable concern for the regulatory reporting market is the impact of significant operational burdens and the continued use of manual and ad hoc processes that result in increased effort and less accurate data.
